<D>__{all right, i will listen.}
<C>__{leon}
<D>__{i know you hate the obvious but do you mind if, at this moment, i'm not in the least subtle?}
<C>__{swana}
<D>__{brutal frankness, if you insist.}
<C>__{leon}
<D>__{there are a hundred ways to approach it, but i feel it can best be said in one simple phrase. i'm in love, swana.}
<C>__{swana}
<D>__{and i thought it was something serious! how could you frighten me so?}
<C>__{leon}
<D>__{it must be serious, swana. not long ago i'd have considered such a statement rather juvenile and rather middle class. now i can say it without stammering, without a blush. i'm in love, swana.}
<C>__{swana}
<D>__{say it over and over again, leon. words are a wonderful safety valve, and that's what you need because you know it's impossible, don't you?}
<C>__{leon}
